5 Apr 2015 Canada: Patient tests negative for Ebola at Toronto hospital
http://www.huffingtonpost.ca/2015/04/05/patient-tests-negative-for-ebola-after-transfer-to-toronto-hospital_n_7006328.html
[A patient who was admitted to Toronto's Sunnybrook hospital with symptoms consistent with the Ebola virus tested negative for the disease. Patient had recently returned from West Africa and was admitted to the Royal Victoria Regional Health Centre in Barrie Saturday morning (4 Apr 2015). In the evening the patient was transferred to Sunnybrook, a designated Ebola response center]

