7 Apr 2015: Sierra Leone police arrest 13 over Ebola fear
http://english.irib.ir/news/world/africa/item/207542-sierra-leone-police-arrest-13-over-ebola-fear
[Arrests were made because of the organizing an illegal funeral for a suspected Ebola victim in Sierra Leone. Security forces stopped the funeral procession of the 50-year-old man on the outskirts of Freetown. Security also issued an alert for the ambulance, which eyewitnesses said brought the corpse to the cemetery.]

6 Apr 2015 UK: Plymouth sailors back from Ebola fight, as ship sails back into West country
http://www.plymouthherald.co.uk/Plymouth-sailors-Ebola-fight-ship-sails/story-26291179-detail/story.html#ixzz3WYhvJppc
[The RFA Argus, a military hospital ship, which is part of the UK's efforts against the Ebola virus in Africa, is back in West Country (UK) waters after a 6-month deployment. The ship will dock at Falmouth 7 Apr 2015. Crew members have already begun to fly ashore.]

7 Apr 2015 USA (Maryland): American Ebola patient improves to good condition
http://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/apr/07/american-ebola-patient-improves-to-good-condition
[Male patient was admitted to National Institutes of Health facility on 13 Mar 2015. Worst status: critical. Patient was working in Sierra Leone, through Partners in Health. About 40 other workers are being monitored as contacts of the NIH patient; none has tested positive as of last week.]

[It is also of note that the Sierra Leone doctor who became ill working alongside this doctor is doing well and recovering from disease after being treated in West Africa - Mod.LK]

