7 Apr 2015 Liberia: Why the report of the Ebola money is necessary
http://allafrica.com/stories/201504071138.html?viewall=1
[Now more than 6 months since the General Auditing Commission (GAC) was requested to make public an audit report for the expenditure of Ebola funding. The initial deadline given the commission has expired, yet the report is not out to the public.]

7 Apr 2015 Liberia: Who is delaying Ebola money report?
http://thenewslib.com/news/highlights/2004-who-delaying-ebola-money-report
The issue of an audit of funding provided by Liberia for the Ebola virus outbreak has become a concern. In September 2014, Bassa County Senator Nyonblee Karnga-Lawrence requested from Senate leadership an inquiry into the extended length of time required by the General Auditing Commission [GAC] to make public its audit report. A letter was sent to the GAC mandating it audit all activities funded by the government of Liberia. The information has not yet been delivered]

8 Apr 2015 UN: envoy thanks PH (Philippine government) for P90M contribution to Ebola fund
